    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-02-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <head>No. 2.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName
                            type="to">Schenck</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 3, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>There must be no withdrawal of any part of the claim presented. Counsel will
                    argue the case as prepared, unless they show to this Government reasons for a
                    change.</p>
                <p>The alarm you speak of does not reach us. We are perfectly calm and content to
                    await the award, and do not anticipate repudiation of the Treaty by the other
                    side.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
